  • Constructor Details

    • Level

      public Level​(java.lang.String fileName) throws java.io.FileNotFoundException, LevelException, VacuumException, SpriteException
      Constructor
      Parameters:
      fileName - Name of the configuration file which has all the information of the level.
      Throws:
      java.io.FileNotFoundException - When it is impossible to open the configuration file.
      LevelException - When the number of rows or columns are zero or negative; when the number of turns or time is negative; when there is not only one vacuum cleaner; when there are not dumpsters; when there are not dirts or dustballs.
      VacuumException - When the value for the vacuum cleaner's capacity is zero or negative.
      SpriteException - When the index of either the row or the column is incorrect.

  • Method Details

    • get1DBoard

      public java.util.List<Sprite> get1DBoard()
      This method returns a 1-D list with all the sprites which are in the board. The rows are concatenated in a sequential order.
      Returns:
      1-D board in the format of a List.

    • getCell

      public Sprite getCell​(int row, int column)
      Retrieve the sprite which is in the cell (row, column). If the index "row" or "column" is invalid, then the index is put in the range of [0,max).
      Parameters:
      row - Index of the row to retrieve.
      column - Index of the column to retrieve.
      Returns:
      Sprite which is in the cell (row, column).

    • setCell

      public void setCell​(Sprite sprite) throws SpriteException
      Sets the "sprite" in the specific cell indicated by sprite's row and column.
      Parameters:
      sprite - Sprite to put into the cell indicated by sprite's row and sprite's column.
      Throws:
      SpriteException - When either the row index or the column index are negative.

    • setCell

      public void setCell​(int row, int column, Sprite sprite) throws SpriteException
      Sets the sprite in a specific (row,column) cell. Updates sprite's row and column information with the data of the parameters "row" and "column". Likewise, it puts the indexes in range of [0,board.max).
      Parameters:
      row - Index of the row in which the sprite must be.
      column - Index of the column in which the sprite must be.
      sprite - Sprite to put into the (row,column) cell.
      Throws:
      SpriteException - When either the row index or the column index are negative.
